SUBROUTINE_BLOCK Q0_0_CTRL:SBR3
TITLE=Library: Micro Automation Positioning - SERVo Q0.0 
// 
// Q0_0_CTRL must be called every scan for the other functions to work
// 
// Limitations: It does not work well if the ramp time is set to less than 0.5 sec. 
// 
// This project is based on the built-in linear PTO function. It uses the manual function to control the speed and the HSC counter to count the pulses. It uses the software HSC interrupt to signal when to start the deceleration ramp instead of the exact pulse count. This reduces the amount of calculations that must be done in the user project but can introduce a deviation in the number of pulses.
// 
// Hardware Resources:
// Q0.0 is used for the high speed pulse output
// Q0.2 is used for the direction output
// The forward and reverse limit switches are set by the user in Q0_0_CTRL
// If the Homing function Q0_0_Home is used then I0.0 is used as the Reference Point position. 
// 
// Advanced calibration option:
// The algorithm that is used to predict when to start the deceleration does not exactly match how the PTO actually works due to software timing issues. This difference is accounted for by the Tune_Factor variable. The optimal value for the Tune_Factor is dependent on the target velocity, Maximum speed, Start/Stop speed, and the maximal Acceleration/Deceleration time. With the default value (Tune_Factor=1) the positioning stops behind the target. To compensate this the bit Disable_Auto_Stop (default value=0) cuts off the deceleration ramp when the target is reached. If the cutting off is unwanted for an application (Disable_Auto_Stop=1) the Tune_Factor has to be modified to stop at the target position.
// Steps to adjust the calibration:
// 	Note: The CPU does not have to be connected to the motor to do this calibration.
// 1.	Turn on the bit Disable_Auto_Stop
// 2.	Load 0 to the current position using Q0_0_LoadPos.
// 3.	Do a relative movement with your parameters (Velocity_SS, Velocity_Max, accel_dec_time, Velocity) and enough 	                Num_Pluses to reach Velocity.
// 4.	Record the current position that is reached. The searched value for this application is:
// 	Tune_Factor = (C_Pos - Num_Pulses + Est_Stopping_Dist) / Est_Stopping_Dist 
// 5.	Control the new value by repeating the relative movement (from step 2). If the value for Tune_Factor is good then 	                the current position should be a few counts beyond the target location. Otherwise you have to reduce the found 	                value a little bit.
// 6.	Add a network after Q0_0_CTRL that moves the new value in the VD location identified in the library as			Tune_Factor on the first scan.  This is necessary because Q0_0_CTRL restores the default value on every first			scan.  You have to use the absolute V address since you can not use the symbol name that is used in the			library.
// 7.	Turn off the bit Disable_Auto_Stop 
// 
// 
// Date: July 16, 2008
// Version:  1.8          
// 
//  The SIMATIC S7-200 Application Tips are provided to give users of the 
//  S7-200 some indication as to how, from the view of programming technique,
//  certain tasks can be solved with this controller. These instructions do not 
//  purport to cover all details or variations in equipment, nor to provide for 
//  every possible contingency. Use of the S7-200 Application Tips is free.
// 
//  Siemens reserves the right to make changes in specifications shown herein
//  or make improvements at any time without notice or obligation. It does not 
//  relieve the user of responsibility to use sound practices in application, 
//  installation, operation and maintenance of the equipment purchased. Should 
//  a conflict arise between the general information contained in this publication
//  and the contents of drawings or supplementary material or both, the latter 
//  shall take precedence.
// 
//  Siemens is not liable, for whatever legal reason, for damages or personal 
//  injury resulting from the use of the application tips.
VAR_INPUT
Velocity_SS:DINT;	// Start/Stop velocity (pulses/sec)
Velocity_Max:DINT;	// Maximum velocity (pulses/sec)
accel_dec_time:REAL;	// Maximum Acceleration and Deceleration time in sec (0.5 to 32.0)
Fwd_Limit:BOOL;	// Limit switch for forward movement
Rev_Limit:BOOL;	// Limit switch for reverse movement
END_VAR
VAR_OUTPUT
C_Pos:DINT;	// Current position (pulses)
END_VAR
VAR
tint:REAL;
fdelta:REAL;
m:INT;
Compute_Rate:DINT;
temp_DI:DINT;
temp_DI2:DINT;
temp_Real:REAL;
temp_I:INT;
END_VAR
BEGIN
Network 1 // This POU is password-protected against editing and viewing.

END_SUBROUTINE_BLOCK
